description:
In this message, we explore one of John’s favorite subjects, abiding. John 15 says, “Abide in me, and I in you. As the branch cannot bear fruit of itself, except it abide in the vine; no more can you, except you abide in me. If you abide in me, and my words abide in you, you shall ask what ye will, and it shall be done unto you.” If we do not abide, we shall be separated from Jesus but, if we abide, we shall bear fruit.
